<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-11-16T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-11-16T16:00:00-05:00" n="101" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d101">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.60D/112a: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Finland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-11-16T17:00:00-04:00">November
                                    16, 1942—5 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>225. We see no objection to your actively circulating among such persons
                            as you think appropriate, the statements that we consider Witting and
                            his Ministry so pro-German that we expect nothing but a continuous
                            worsening of relations with Finland as long as he remains in office and
                            that it is out of the question to expect any <hi rend="italic">rapprochement</hi> with the United States until he is replaced by a
                            person in whom we can have some confidence.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>